%I A391119 #65 May 10 2026 21:41:58
%S A391119 110,2,1,4,2,2,2,3,2,2,3,1,3,1,2,1,2,3,1,2,4,1,3,2,4,4,1,2,1,10,2,1,2,
%T A391119 2,4,1,1,2,1,1,2,4,4,3,7,2,1,4,3,2,1,2,5,1,1,1,3,1,1,6,8,4,4,3,6,3,1,
%U A391119 1,8,3,1,2,1,1,3,1,2,2,7,2,2,2,3,1,1,1
%N A391119 a(n) is the involvement delay of prime(n) in A390812.
%C A391119 Here "involvement" means that n is in a pair that is counted in A390812(k). The "delay" is the minimal k minus n.
%H A391119 Ruud H.G. van Tol, <a href="/A391119/b391119.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A391119 a(1) = 110 because prime(1) gets first involved at A390812(1+110), for the line through (1, 2; 103, 563; 111, 607).
%e A391119 a(8) = 3 because prime(8) gets first involved at A390812(8+3), for the line through (8, 19; 9, 23; 11, 31).
%o A391119 (PARI) a(n)= for(i=n+1, oo, my(p=primes(i), r=(p[i]-p[n])/(i-n)); for(j=1, i-1, if(j!=n && r==(p[i]-p[j])/(i-j), return(i-n))));
%Y A391119 Cf. A390812.
%K A391119 nonn,new
%O A391119 1,1
%A A391119 _Ruud H.G. van Tol_, Apr 24 2026
